Malawi’s Inflation Fell to 7.1% in April on Food Costs

-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 
2011-05-21T11:43:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-21/malawi-s-inflation-fell-to-7-1-in-april-on-food-costs-1-.html
Malawi’s annual inflation rate
decelerated to 7.1 percent in April, from 7.2 percent in March,
following a drop in food prices, the country’s National
Statistics Agency said in a faxed statement today.  Food inflation has gone down from 6.3 percent for the same
period last year, the Zomba-based agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
